casebody.data:
Janet RODRIGUEZ, Appellant,
v.
ALS COMMERCIAL FUNDING, LLC, Appellee. No. 3D18-1709 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Third District. Opinion filed May 1, 2019. Janet Rodriguez, in proper person. Bassett Law Firm, P.A., and Heidi J. Bassett (Tampa); Daniel Y. Gielchinsky, P.A., and Daniel Y. Gielchinsky, Aventura, for appellee. Before EMAS, C.J., and LINDSEY and HENDON, JJ. HENDON, J.

Having reviewed the appellant's initial brief, this court finds that there exists no preliminary basis for reversal of the cause below. We affirm pursuant to Florida Rule of Appellate Procedure 9.315(a).

Affirmed.
